title: For Sale/Trade:  Sig Sauer556 piston operated with many extras
postcontent:
I have a very nice and extremely accurate Sig Sauer556 piston operated rifle chambered in 5.56 nato. It features ambi-controls and a front 2-position gas switch, rear flip-up peep sight and loads of rail space. The rifle is in like new condition with a low round count. It comes with the original case and all paperwork along with 6 sig sauer 30 round magazines. all the mags come with sig couplers so you essentially have 3 - 60 round mags. I am the original owner and it has been very well taken care of. If you're not familiar with this model, it is very close to a Ak-47 platform. It is more modern and refined but the only other real difference between the two is the sigs recoil spring and piston are one piece whereas on the Ak, the spring rides above the piston. These are no longer in production...replaced with a much lighter (and way less solid) sig M400...don't miss out on this incredibly sweet and increasingly hard to find battle rifle. Asking $1200 and I will include some quality ammo with the deal. looking for cash to fund another project but I would consider a partial trade on a nice 9mm or .45acp handgun.  Please email or text for additional pics or more info.

Revolver made around the turn of the 20th century (has patent dates stamped into the barrel rib of 1870-80's) One of the first "pocket guns", the idea behind making a gun with a enclosed hammer, was to keep it from snagging on your clothing while pocket carrying, thus the nick name "Safety Hammerless."
